The BRIDGES Programme, which is a part of the Mastercard Foundation's Young Africa Works in Ethiopia strategy, and is being implemented in partnership with First Consult, has signed a Memorandum of Understanding with the Ministry of Trade and Industry that will lead to significant work opportunities for young people in Ethiopia. The collaboration will focus on enhancing the competitiveness of the industrial sector to attract qualified workers and will offer support to existing micro, small, and medium enterprises (MSMEs).  Find out more about Mastercard Foundation in Africa.